---
---
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="utf-8" />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
        <title>de Laval Nozzle CFD · Marcus</title>
        <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
        <link
            href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Serif+Display&family=DM+Mono:wght@400;500&family=DM+Sans:wght@400;500&display=swap"
            rel="stylesheet"
        />
    </head>
    <body>
        <div id="wrapper">
            <nav>
                <span class="nav-name">Marcus David Yang | Aerospace Engineer @ UIUC</span>
                <div class="nav-links">
                    <a href="/">Home</a>
                </div>
            </nav>

            <a href="/" class="back-link">← projects</a>

            <section class="hero">
                <p class="hero-label">Aerospace · May 2026</p>
                <h1>CFD Analysis of a<br />de Laval Nozzle</h1>
                <p class="hero-date">5.29.26</p>
                <p class="hero-desc">
                    Designed and analyzed a converging-diverging (de Laval) nozzle using
                    Siemens NX, SpaceClaim, ANSYS Meshing, and ANSYS Fluent.
                </p>
                <button id="open-modal-btn" class="data-btn">
                    View simulation data ↗
                </button>
            </section>

            <!-- Meshing -->
            <p class="section-label">Meshing</p>
            <div class="content-block">
                <p>
                    Generated an unstructured tetrahedral mesh with local
                    refinement near the throat to accurately capture the strong
                    gradients in the transonic region.
                </p>
                <div class="image-single">
                    <img src="/images/de-laval-nozzle-mesh.png" alt="Nozzle mesh" />
                    <p class="img-caption">Unstructured tetrahedral mesh — full 3-D geometry. Finer elements concentrate at the throat (~0.15–0.30 m) where velocity and pressure gradients are steepest.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Velocity -->
            <p class="section-label">Velocity</p>
            <div class="content-block">
                <p>
                    A density-based compressible solver in ANSYS Fluent was configured
                    with a subsonic pressure inlet and supersonic pressure outlet.
                    Flow accelerates dramatically through the throat, reaching peak
                    exit velocities above 590 m/s.
                </p>
                <div class="image-single">
                    <img src="/images/velocity-magnitude.png" alt="Velocity magnitude mid-plane cross-section" />
                    <p class="img-caption">Velocity magnitude — mid-plane cross-section. Flow accelerates from ~60 m/s (blue) in the converging section through the throat, reaching >590 m/s (red) in the diverging section. A thin boundary layer is visible along the diverging wall.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="image-row two-col" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
                    <figure>
                        <img src="/images/inlet-velocity-magnitude.png" alt="Inlet velocity contour" />
                        <figcaption>Inlet velocity magnitude — near-uniform low-velocity inflow (0–180 m/s) confirms a well-conditioned pressure inlet with minimal recirculation.</figcaption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure>
                        <img src="/images/outlet-velocity-magnitude.png" alt="Outlet velocity contour" />
                        <figcaption>Outlet velocity magnitude — peak core velocities ~590 m/s (red), with a thin low-velocity annulus at the wall edge from boundary-layer growth over the diverging section.</figcaption>
                    </figure>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Mach Number -->
            <p class="section-label">Mach Number</p>
            <div class="content-block">
                <p>
                    Mach contours confirm classic converging–diverging behaviour: subsonic
                    inflow, sonic conditions at the throat, and fully supersonic exit flow
                    reaching M ≈ 2.61. The Mach vs. position plot shows the smooth
                    isentropic acceleration profile with no normal shock in the diverging section.
                </p>
                <div class="image-row two-col">
                    <figure>
                        <img src="/images/mach-contour.png" alt="Mach number cross-section" />
                        <figcaption>Mach number — mid-plane cross-section. Subsonic inlet (M ≈ 0.30, blue), sonic throat (M = 1), supersonic exit (M ≈ 2.61, red). Smooth gradient indicates an attached, shock-free solution.</figcaption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure>
                        <img src="/images/mach-vs-position.png" alt="Mach number vs axial position" />
                        <figcaption>Mach number vs. axial position — each line traces a streamline through plane-3. Throat at ~0.40 m; M = 1 crossed cleanly before diverging to ~2.5 at exit.</figcaption>
                    </figure>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Pressure -->
            <p class="section-label">Pressure</p>
            <div class="content-block">
                <p>
                    Absolute pressure drops sharply through the throat as kinetic energy
                    increases, consistent with isentropic flow theory. The inlet-to-outlet
                    pressure ratio of ~16:1 is characteristic of M ≈ 2.6 expansion.
                </p>
                <div class="image-single">
                    <img src="/images/pressure-cross-section.png" alt="Absolute pressure mid-plane cross-section" />
                    <p class="img-caption">Absolute pressure — mid-plane cross-section. High pressure at inlet (~2.81 × 10⁵ Pa, red) drops sharply at the throat and continues falling through the diverging section to ~1.44 × 10⁴ Pa (blue) at exit.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 1rem;">
                    <div class="image-single">
                        <img src="/images/pressure-vs-position.png" alt="Static pressure vs axial position" />
                        <p class="img-caption">Static pressure vs. axial position — pressure falls steeply at the throat (~0.30–0.45 m) and levels off in the supersonic diverging region. Note: gauge pressure goes negative downstream of the throat relative to the outlet back-pressure.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Temperature -->
            <p class="section-label">Temperature</p>
            <div class="content-block">
                <p>
                    Total temperature remains nearly uniform throughout the nozzle
                    (298–303 K), confirming adiabatic wall conditions and an
                    energy-conserving solution. The peak near the throat reflects
                    local viscous dissipation in the boundary layer.
                </p>
                <div class="image-row two-col">
                    <figure>
                        <img src="/images/temp-cross-section.png" alt="Total temperature mid-plane cross-section" />
                        <figcaption>Total temperature — mid-plane cross-section. Variation is narrow (298–303 K), with a warm band at the throat boundary layer, confirming near-isentropic conditions in the core flow.</figcaption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure>
                        <img src="/images/temp-walls.png" alt="Total temperature on nozzle walls" />
                        <figcaption>Total temperature — 3-D wall surface. The throat ring shows peak total temperature (~303 K, red-orange) driven by viscous heating in the boundary layer, tapering toward cooler values at inlet and exit faces.</figcaption>
                    </figure>
                </div>
            </div>

            <footer>
                <p>marcus · summer 2026</p>
                <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/marcusdyang" target="_blank">LinkedIn ↗</a>
                <a href="https://github.com" target="_blank">github ↗</a>
            </footer>
        </div>

        <!-- Data Modal -->
        <div id="modal-backdrop"></div>
        <div id="data-modal" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-label="Simulation Data">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <div>
                    <p class="modal-label">ANSYS Fluent · Surface Integral Reports</p>
                    <h2 class="modal-title">Simulation Data</h2>
                </div>
                <button id="close-modal-btn" class="modal-close" aria-label="Close">✕</button>
            </div>
            <p class="modal-desc">
                Area-weighted averages exported directly from ANSYS Fluent post-processing.
                All values are steady-state results from the density-based compressible solver.
            </p>
            <div class="data-table-wrap">
                <table class="data-table">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Metric</th>
                            <th>Surface</th>
                            <th>Value</th>
                            <th>Unit</th>
                            <th>Report type</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Exit Velocity Magnitude</td>
                            <td><span class="surface-pill outlet">outlet</span></td>
                            <td class="val">569.562</td>
                            <td class="unit">m/s</td>
                            <td class="type">Area-Weighted Avg</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Inlet Absolute Pressure</td>
                            <td><span class="surface-pill inlet">inlet</span></td>
                            <td class="val">279,377</td>
                            <td class="unit">Pa</td>
                            <td class="type">Area-Weighted Avg</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Outlet Mass Flow Rate</td>
                            <td><span class="surface-pill outlet">outlet</span></td>
                            <td class="val">−18.907</td>
                            <td class="unit">kg/s</td>
                            <td class="type">Mass Flow Rate</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Outlet Absolute Pressure</td>
                            <td><span class="surface-pill outlet">outlet</span></td>
                            <td class="val">17,446</td>
                            <td class="unit">Pa</td>
                            <td class="type">Area-Weighted Avg</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Wall Static Temperature</td>
                            <td><span class="surface-pill wall">walls</span></td>
                            <td class="val">287.027</td>
                            <td class="unit">K</td>
                            <td class="type">Area-Weighted Avg</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Wall Total Temperature</td>
                            <td><span class="surface-pill wall">walls</span></td>
                            <td class="val">300.425</td>
                            <td class="unit">K</td>
                            <td class="type">Area-Weighted Avg</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-notes">
                <p class="modal-notes-label">Notes</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Negative mass flow rate at outlet is a Fluent sign convention — flow is <em>leaving</em> the domain.</li>
                    <li>Inlet-to-outlet pressure ratio: 279,377 / 17,446 ≈ <strong>16.0</strong>, consistent with M ≈ 2.6 isentropic expansion.</li>
                    <li>Wall total temperature (300.4 K) closely matches standard sea-level T₀ = 300 K, confirming adiabatic wall boundary conditions.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <style>
            * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

            body {
                font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
                background: #fafaf9;
                color: #1a1a18;
            }

            #wrapper {
                width: 100%;
                max-width: 860px;
                margin-left: auto;
                margin-right: auto;
                padding-left: 80px;
                padding-right: 80px;
            }

            nav {
                display: flex;
                justify-content: space-between;
                align-items: center;
                padding-top: 2.5rem;
                padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
                border-bottom: 1px solid #e0dfd8;
                margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
            }

            .nav-name {
                font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
                font-size: 14px;
                font-weight: 500;
                letter-spacing: 0.04em;
            }

            .nav-links { display: flex; gap: 2rem; }

            .nav-links a {
                font-size: 14px;
                color: #888780;
                text-decoration: none;
            }

            .nav-links a:hover { color: #1a1a18; }

            .back-link {
                display: inline-block;
                font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
                font-size: 12px;
                color: #888780;
                text-decoration: none;
                letter-spacing: 0.04em;
                margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
            }

            .back-link:hover { color: #1a1a18; }

            .hero { margin-bottom: 5rem; }

            .hero-label {
                font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
                font-size: 12px;
                color: #b4b2a9;
                letter-spacing: 0.08em;
                text-transform: uppercase;
                margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
            }

            .hero h1 {
                font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
                font-size: 44px;
                font-weight: 400;
                line-height: 1.15;
                margin-bottom: 1rem;
            }

            .hero-date {
                font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
                font-size: 12px;
                color: #b4b2a9;
                margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
            }

            .hero-desc {
                font-size: 16px;
                color: #5f5e5a;
                line-height: 1.7;
                max-width: 480px;
                margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
            }

            .data-btn {
                font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
                font-size: 12px;
                letter-spacing: 0.04em;
                padding: 8px 18px;
                border: 1px solid #1a1a18;
                border-radius: 6px;
                background: transparent;
                color: #1a1a18;
                cursor: pointer;
                transition: background 0.15s, color 0.15s;
            }

            .data-btn:hover {
                background: #1a1a18;
                color: #fafaf9;
            }

            .section-label {
                font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
                font-size: 11px;
                color: #b4b2a9;
                letter-spacing: 0.1em;
                text-transform: uppercase;
                margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
            }

            .content-block { margin-bottom: 4.5rem; }

            .content-block > p {
                font-size: 15px;
                color: #5f5e5a;
                line-height: 1.75;
                max-width: 560px;
                margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            }

            .image-single {
                border: 1px solid #e0dfd8;
                border-radius: 12px;
                overflow: hidden;
                background: #f1efea;
            }

            .image-single img {
                display: block;
                width: 100%;
                height: auto;
            }

            .img-caption {
                padding: 0.9rem 1.25rem 1rem;
                font-size: 12px;
                color: #888780;
                line-height: 1.6;
                border-top: 1px solid #e0dfd8;
            }

            .image-row {
                border: 1px solid #e0dfd8;
                border-radius: 12px;
                overflow: hidden;
                background: #e0dfd8;
            }

            .image-row.two-col {
                display: grid;
                grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
                gap: 1px;
            }

            .image-row figure {
                background: #f1efea;
                display: flex;
                flex-direction: column;
            }

            .image-row figure img {
                display: block;
                width: 100%;
                height: 210px;
                object-fit: cover;
            }

            .image-row figcaption {
                padding: 0.9rem 1.1rem 1rem;
                font-size: 12px;
                color: #888780;
                line-height: 1.6;
                flex: 1;
                border-top: 1px solid #e0dfd8;
            }

            footer {
                padding-top: 2rem;
                padding-bottom: 3rem;
                border-top: 1px solid #e0dfd8;
                display: flex;
                justify-content: space-between;
                align-items: center;
            }

            footer p, footer a {
                font-size: 13px;
                color: #b4b2a9;
                font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
                text-decoration: none;
            }

            footer a:hover { color: #1a1a18; }

            #modal-backdrop {
                display: none;
                position: fixed;
                inset: 0;
                background: rgba(26, 26, 24, 0.35);
                backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
                z-index: 100;
            }

            #modal-backdrop.open { display: block; }

            #data-modal {
                position: fixed;
                top: 0;
                right: 0;
                bottom: 0;
                width: min(600px, 100vw);
                background: #fafaf9;
                border-left: 1px solid #e0dfd8;
                z-index: 101;
                overflow-y: auto;
                padding: 2.5rem 2.25rem;
                transform: translateX(100%);
                transition: transform 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
            }

            #data-modal.open { transform: translateX(0); }

            .modal-header {
                display: flex;
                justify-content: space-between;
                align-items: flex-start;
                margin-bottom: 1rem;
            }

            .modal-label {
                font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
                font-size: 10px;
                color: #b4b2a9;
                letter-spacing: 0.08em;
                text-transform: uppercase;
                margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
            }

            .modal-title {
                font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
                font-size: 24px;
                font-weight: 400;
            }

            .modal-close {
                background: none;
                border: 1px solid #e0dfd8;
                border-radius: 6px;
                width: 32px;
                height: 32px;
                display: flex;
                align-items: center;
                justify-content: center;
                cursor: pointer;
                font-size: 13px;
                color: #888780;
                flex-shrink: 0;
                margin-top: 4px;
            }

            .modal-close:hover { border-color: #1a1a18; color: #1a1a18; }

            .modal-desc {
                font-size: 13px;
                color: #5f5e5a;
                line-height: 1.7;
                margin-bottom: 2rem;
                padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
                border-bottom: 1px solid #e0dfd8;
            }

            .data-table-wrap {
                overflow-x: auto;
                margin-bottom: 2rem;
            }

            .data-table {
                width: 100%;
                border-collapse: collapse;
                font-size: 13px;
            }

            .data-table thead tr { border-bottom: 1px solid #e0dfd8; }

            .data-table th {
                font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
                font-size: 10px;
                font-weight: 500;
                letter-spacing: 0.07em;
                text-transform: uppercase;
                color: #b4b2a9;
                padding: 0 0.75rem 0.75rem 0;
                text-align: left;
                white-space: nowrap;
            }

            .data-table td {
                padding: 0.9rem 0.75rem 0.9rem 0;
                border-bottom: 1px solid #f0eee8;
                color: #1a1a18;
                vertical-align: middle;
            }

            .data-table tbody tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
            .data-table tbody tr:hover td { background: #f4f2ec; }

            td.val {
                font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
                font-size: 13px;
                font-weight: 500;
                white-space: nowrap;
            }

            td.unit {
                font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
                font-size: 11px;
                color: #888780;
                white-space: nowrap;
            }

            td.type {
                font-size: 11px;
                color: #b4b2a9;
                white-space: nowrap;
            }

            .surface-pill {
                font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
                font-size: 10px;
                padding: 2px 8px;
                border-radius: 4px;
                white-space: nowrap;
            }

            .surface-pill.outlet { background: #E6F1FB; color: #185FA5; }
            .surface-pill.inlet  { background: #E1F5EE; color: #0F6E56; }
            .surface-pill.wall   { background: #FDF3E3; color: #9A5B10; }

            .modal-notes {
                border-top: 1px solid #e0dfd8;
                padding-top: 1.5rem;
            }

            .modal-notes-label {
                font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
                font-size: 10px;
                letter-spacing: 0.08em;
                text-transform: uppercase;
                color: #b4b2a9;
                margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
            }

            .modal-notes ul {
                list-style: none;
                display: flex;
                flex-direction: column;
                gap: 0.6rem;
            }

            .modal-notes li {
                font-size: 12px;
                color: #5f5e5a;
                line-height: 1.65;
                padding-left: 1rem;
                position: relative;
            }

            .modal-notes li::before {
                content: '–';
                position: absolute;
                left: 0;
                color: #b4b2a9;
            }

            .modal-notes strong { color: #1a1a18; font-weight: 500; }
        </style>

        <script>
            const modal = document.getElementById('data-modal');
            const backdrop = document.getElementById('modal-backdrop');
            const openBtn = document.getElementById('open-modal-btn');
            const closeBtn = document.getElementById('close-modal-btn');

            function openModal() {
                modal.classList.add('open');
                backdrop.classList.add('open');
                document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden';
            }

            function closeModal() {
                modal.classList.remove('open');
                backdrop.classList.remove('open');
                document.body.style.overflow = '';
            }

            openBtn.addEventListener('click', openModal);
            closeBtn.addEventListener('click', closeModal);
            backdrop.addEventListener('click', closeModal);

            document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
                if (e.key === 'Escape') closeModal();
            });
        </script>
    </body>
</html>
